<h2 id="2-m·ªôt-ch√∫t-to√°n">2. M·ªôt ch√∫t to√°n</h2>

<p><a name="-norm--cua-ma-tran"></a></p>

<h3 id="21-norm-2-c·ªßa-ma-tr·∫≠n">2.1. Norm 2 c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n</h3>
<p>Ch√∫ng ta v·∫´n th∆∞·ªùng nh·∫Øc nhi·ªÅu ƒë·∫øn <a href="http://machinelearningcoban.com/math/#-norms-chuan">norm cho vector</a> nh∆∞ng ch∆∞a th·ª±c s·ª± l√†m vi·ªác nhi·ªÅu v·ªõi norm c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n (ngo√†i <a href="http://machinelearningcoban.com/math/#chuan-cua-ma-tran">Frobenius norm</a>). Trong m·ª•c n√†y, ch√∫ng ta s·∫Ω l√†m quen v·ªõi 1 l·ªõp c√°c norm cho ma tr·∫≠n ƒë∆∞·ª£c ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a d·ª±a tr√™n norm c·ªßa vector. L·ªõp c√°c norms n√†y c√≤n ƒë∆∞·ª£c g·ªçi l√† <em>Induced Norms</em>.</p>

<p>Gi·∫£ s·ª≠ h√†m s·ªë \(||\mathbf{x}||_{\alpha}\) l√† m·ªôt norm b·∫•t k·ª≥ c·ªßa vector \(\mathbf{x}\). ·ª®ng v·ªõi norm n√†y, ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a norm t∆∞∆°ng ·ª©ng cho ma tr·∫≠n \(\mathbf{A}\):
\[
||\mathbf{A}||_{\alpha} = \max_{\mathbf{x}} \frac{||\mathbf{Ax}||_{\alpha}}{||\mathbf{x}||_{\alpha}}
\]</p>

<p>ch√∫ √Ω r·∫±ng ma tr·∫≠n \(\mathbf{A}\) c√≥ th·ªÉ kh√¥ng vu√¥ng v√† s·ªë c·ªôt c·ªßa n√≥ b·∫±ng v·ªõi s·ªë chi·ªÅu c·ªßa \(\mathbf{x}\). Nh∆∞ v·∫≠y, b·∫£n th√¢n vi·ªác t√≠nh to√°n norm c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n l√† vi·ªác gi·∫£i m·ªôt b√†i to√°n t·ªëi ∆∞u. Ch√∫ √Ω r·∫±ng h√†m t·ªëi ∆∞u c√≥ c·∫£ t·ª≠ s·ªë v√† m·∫´u s·ªë l√† c√°c norm tr√™n vectors.</p>

<p>Ch√∫ng ta s·∫Ω quan t√¢m nhi·ªÅu h∆°n t·ªõi norm 2. Norm 2 c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n ƒë∆∞·ª£c ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a l√†:
\[
||\mathbf{A}||_2 = \max_{\mathbf{x}} \frac{||\mathbf{Ax}||_2}{||\mathbf{x}||_2} ~~~ (1)
\]</p>

<p>Nh·∫≠n th·∫•y r·∫±ng n·∫øu \(\mathbf{x}\) l√† nghi·ªám c·ªßa b√†i to√°n t·ªëi ∆∞u \((1)\) th√¨ \(k\mathbf{x}\) c≈©ng l√† nghi·ªám v·ªõi \(k\) l√† m·ªôt s·ªë th·ª±c kh√°c kh√¥ng b·∫•t k·ª≥. Kh√¥ng m·∫•t t√≠nh t·ªïng qu√°t, ta c√≥ th·ªÉ gi·∫£ s·ª≠ m·∫´u s·ªë b·∫±ng 1. Khi ƒë√≥, b√†i to√°n t·ªëi ∆∞u \((1)\) c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒë∆∞·ª£c vi·∫øt d∆∞·ªõi d·∫°ng:
\[
||\mathbf{A}||_2 = \max_{||\mathbf{x}||_2 = 1} ||\mathbf{Ax}||_2 ~~~ (2)
\]
N√≥i c√°ch kh√°c, ta c·∫ßn ƒëi t√¨m \(\mathbf{x}\) sao cho:
\[
\begin{eqnarray}
\mathbf{x} &amp;=&amp; \text{argmax}_{\mathbf{x}} ||\mathbf{Ax}||_2^2 &amp; \newline
\text{s.t.: } &amp;&amp; ||\mathbf{x}||_2^2 = 1 &amp; (3)
\end{eqnarray}
\]
·ªû ƒë√¢y, c√°c norm 2 ƒë√£ ƒë∆∞·ª£c b√¨nh ph∆∞∆°ng l√™n ƒë·ªÉ tr√°nh d·∫•u cƒÉn b·∫≠c hai. B√†i to√°n \((3)\) c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒë∆∞·ª£c gi·∫£i b·∫±ng <a href="/2017/04/02/duality/#--phuong-phap-nhan-tu-lagrange">Ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p nh√¢n t·ª≠ Lagrange</a> v√¨ r√†ng bu·ªôc l√† m·ªôt ph∆∞∆°ng tr√¨nh.</p>

<p>Lagrangian c·ªßa B√†i to√°n \((3)\) l√†:
\[
\mathcal{L}(\mathbf{x}, \lambda) = ||\mathbf{Ax}||_2^2 + \lambda (1 - ||\mathbf{x}||_2^2)
\]</p>

<p>Nghi·ªám c·ªßa b√†i to√°n \((3)\) s·∫Ω tho·∫£ m√£n h·ªá ph∆∞∆°ng tr√¨nh:
\[
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{\partial \mathcal{L}}{\partial \mathbf{x}} &amp;=&amp; 2\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{Ax} - 2\lambda \mathbf{x} = \mathbf{0} &amp; (4)\newline
\frac{\partial \mathcal{L}}{\partial \lambda} &amp;=&amp; 1 - ||\mathbf{x}||_2^2 = 0 &amp; (5)
\end{eqnarray}
\]</p>

<p>T·ª´ \((4)\) ta c√≥:
\[
\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{Ax} = \lambda\mathbf{x} ~~~~ (6)
\]
ƒêi·ªÅu n√†y suy ra r·∫±ng \(\lambda\) l√† m·ªôt tr·ªã ri√™ng c·ªßa \(\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{A}\) v√† \(\mathbf{x}\) l√† 1 vector ri√™ng ·ª©ng v·ªõi tr·ªã ri√™ng ƒë√≥. Ti·∫øp t·ª•c nh√¢n hai v·∫ø c·ªßa \((6)\) v·ªõi \(\mathbf{x}^T\) v√†o b√™n tr√°i, ta c√≥:
\[
\mathbf{x}^T\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{Ax} = \lambda \mathbf{x}^T\mathbf{x} = \lambda
\]
Nh·∫≠n th·∫•y r·∫±ng v·∫ø tr√°i ch√≠nh l√† \(||\mathbf{Ax}||_2^2\) ch√≠nh l√† h√†m m·ª•c ti√™u trong \((3)\). V·∫≠y h√†m m·ª•c ti√™u ƒë·∫°t gi√° tr·ªã l·ªõn nh·∫•t khi \(\lambda\) ƒë·∫°t gi√° tr·ªã l·ªõn nh·∫•t. N√≥i c√°ch kh√°c, \(\lambda\) ch√≠nh l√† tr·ªã ri√™ng l·ªõn nh·∫•t c·ªßa \(\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{A}\) hay ch√≠nh l√† <a href="/2017/06/07/svd/#-nguon-goc-ten-goi-singular-value-decomposition">singular value</a> l·ªõn nh·∫•t c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n \(\mathbf{A}\).</p>

<p>Nh∆∞ v·∫≠y, norm 2 c·ªßa m·ªôt ma tr·∫≠n ch√≠nh l√† singular value l·ªõn nh·∫•t c·ªßa ma tr·∫≠n ƒë√≥. V√† nghi·ªám c·ªßa b√†i to√°n \((3)\) ch√≠nh m·ªôt l√† <em>right-singular vector</em> ·ª©ng v·ªõi singular value ƒë√≥.</p>

<p>V·ªõi l√Ω lu·∫≠n t∆∞∆°ng t·ª±, ch√∫ng ta c√≥ th·ªÉ suy ra r·∫±ng b√†i to√°n:
\[
\min_{||\mathbf{x}||_2 =1} \mathbf{x}^T\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{A}\mathbf{x}
\]</p>

<p>c√≥ nghi·ªám l√† vector ri√™ng ·ª©ng v·ªõi tr·ªã ri√™ng nh·ªè nh·∫•t c·ªßa \(\mathbf{A}^T\mathbf{A}\). Khi ƒë√≥, h√†m s·ªë ƒë·∫°t gi√° tr·ªã nh·ªè nh·∫•t b·∫±ng ch√≠nh tr·ªã ri√™ng nh·ªè nh·∫•t n√†y.</p>

<p><a name="ky-vong-va-ma-tran-hiep-phuong-sai"></a></p>

<p><a name="-bieu-dien-vector-trong-cac-he-co-so-khac-nhau"></a></p>

<h3 id="22-bi·ªÖu-di·ªÖn-vector-trong-c√°c-h·ªá-c∆°-s·ªü-kh√°c-nhau">2.2. Bi·ªÖu di·ªÖn vector trong c√°c h·ªá c∆° s·ªü kh√°c nhau</h3>

<p>Trong kh√¥ng gian \(D\) chi·ªÅu , to·∫° ƒë·ªô c·ªßa m·ªói ƒëi·ªÉm ƒë∆∞·ª£c x√°c ƒë·ªãnh d·ª±a tr√™n m·ªôt h·ªá to·∫° ƒë·ªô n√†o ƒë√≥. ·ªû c√°c h·ªá to·∫° ƒë·ªô kh√°c nhau, hi·ªÉn nhi√™n l√† to·∫° ƒë·ªô c·ªßa m·ªói ƒëi·ªÉm c≈©ng kh√°c nhau.</p>

<p>T·∫≠p h·ª£p c√°c vector \(\mathbf{e}_1, \dots, \mathbf{e}_D\) m√† m·ªói vector \(\mathbf{e}_d\) c√≥ ƒë√∫ng 1 ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ kh√°c 0 ·ªü th√†nh ph·∫ßn th·ª© \(d\) v√† ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ ƒë√≥ b·∫±ng 1, ƒë∆∞·ª£c g·ªçi l√† h·ªá c∆° s·ªü ƒë∆°n v·ªã (ho·∫∑c h·ªá ƒë∆°n v·ªã) trong kh√¥ng gian \(D\) chi·ªÅu. N·∫øu x·∫øp c√°c vector \(\mathbf{e}_d, d = 1, 2, \dots, D\) theo ƒë√∫ng th·ª© t·ª± ƒë√≥, ta s·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ª£c ma tr·∫≠n ƒë∆°n v·ªã \(D\) chi·ªÅu.</p>

<p>M·ªói vector c·ªôt \(\mathbf{x} = [x_1, x_2, \dots, x_D] \in \mathbb{R}^D\), bi·ªÉu di·ªÖn c·ªßa n√≥ trong h·ªá ƒë∆°n v·ªã l√†:</p>

<p>\[
\mathbf{x} = x_1 \mathbf{e}_1 + x_2 \mathbf{e}_2 + \dots + x_D\mathbf{e}_D
\]</p>

<p>Gi·∫£ s·ª≠ c√≥ m·ªôt h·ªá c∆° s·ªü kh√°c \(\mathbf{u}_1, \mathbf{u}_2, \dots, \mathbf{u}_D\) (c√°c vector n√†y ƒë·ªôc l·∫≠p tuy·∫øn t√≠nh), v·∫≠y th√¨ bi·ªÉu di·ªÖn c·ªßa vector \(\mathbf{x}\) trong h·ªá c∆° s·ªü m·ªõi n√†y c√≥ d·∫°ng:</p>

<p>\[
\mathbf{x} = y_1 \mathbf{u}_1 + y_2 \mathbf{u}_2 + \dots + y_D\mathbf{u}_D  = \mathbf{U}\mathbf{y}
\]</p>

<p>\(\mathbf{U}\) l√† ma tr·∫≠n m√† c·ªôt th·ª© \(d\) c·ªßa n√≥ ch√≠nh l√† vector \(\mathbf{u}_d\). L√∫c n√†y, vector \(\mathbf{y}\) ch√≠nh l√† bi·ªÉu di·ªÖn c·ªßa \(\mathbf{x}\) trong h·ªá c∆° s·ªü m·ªõi. B·ªô c√°c s·ªë \(y_d, d = 1, 2, \dots, D\) l√† duy nh·∫•t v√¨ \(\mathbf{y}\) c√≥ th·ªÉ t√≠nh ƒë∆∞·ª£c b·∫±ng:
\[
\mathbf{y} = \mathbf{U}^{-1} \mathbf{x} ~~~ (7)
\]
v·ªõi ch√∫ √Ω r·∫±ng \(\mathbf{U}\) l√† ma tr·∫≠n kh·∫£ ngh·ªãch v√¨ c√°c c·ªôt c·ªßa n√≥ ƒë·ªôc l·∫≠p tuy·∫øn t√≠nh.</p>

<p>Trong c√°c ma tr·∫≠n ƒë√≥ng vai tr√≤ nh∆∞ h·ªá c∆° s·ªü \(\mathbf{U}\), <a href="/2017/06/07/svd/#-he-truc-giao-va-truc-chuan">c√°c ma tr·∫≠n tr·ª±c giao</a>, t·ª©c \(\mathbf{U}^T\mathbf{U} = \mathbf{I}\), ƒë∆∞·ª£c quan t√¢m nhi·ªÅu h∆°n v√¨ ngh·ªãch ƒë·∫£o c·ªßa ch√∫ng ch√≠nh l√† chuy·ªÉn v·ªã c·ªßa ch√∫ng:</p>

<p>\[
\mathbf{U}^{-1} = \mathbf{U}^T
\]
Khi ƒë√≥, \(\mathbf{y}\) trong \((7)\) c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒë∆∞·ª£c t√≠nh m·ªôt c√°ch nhanh ch√≥ng:</p>

<p>\[
\mathbf{y} = \mathbf{U}^{T} \mathbf{x}
\]
t·ª´ ƒë√≥ suy ra: \(y_i = \mathbf{x}^T \mathbf{u}_i = \mathbf{u}_i^T\mathbf{x}, i= 1, 2, \dots, D\).</p>

<p>C√≥ th·ªÉ nh·∫≠n th·∫•y r·∫±ng vector \(\mathbf{0}\) ƒë∆∞·ª£c bi·ªÉu di·ªÖn nh∆∞ nhau trong m·ªçi h·ªá c∆° s·ªü.
H√¨nh 1 d∆∞·ªõi ƒë√¢y l√† 1 v√≠ d·ª• v·ªÅ vi·ªác chuy·ªÉn h·ªá c∆° s·ªü:</p>

<hr />

<div>
<table width="100%" style="border: 0px solid white">

    <tr>
        <td width="40%" style="border: 0px solid white" align="center">
        <img style="display:block;" width="100%" src="/assets/27_pca/changebasis.png" />
         </td>
        <td width="40%" style="border: 0px solid white" align="justify">
        H√¨nh 1: Chuy·ªÉn ƒë·ªïi to·∫° ƒë·ªô trong c√°c h·ªá c∆° s·ªü kh√°c nhau.

        </td>
    </tr>
